In .NET 10 (starting with .NET 9 SR10+), `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` was deprecated on Android because the underlying `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` flag was removed by Android itself.

The recommended replacement is to use **edge-to-edge display with keyboard (IME) insets**. Here's the approach:

### 1. Enable edge-to-edge + IME handling in your `MainActivity`

```csharp
// Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;

protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
{
    base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

    // Opt into edge-to-edge
    WindowCompat.SetDecorFitsSystemWindows(Window!, false);

    // Listen for keyboard (IME) insets and adjust padding
    ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(Window!.DecorView, new InsetsListener());
}

private class InsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
{
    public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(Android.Views.View v, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
    {
        var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
        var systemBars = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.SystemBars());

        // Push content up by whichever is larger: keyboard or nav bar
        v.SetPadding(
            systemBars.Left,
            systemBars.Top,
            systemBars.Right,
            Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, systemBars.Bottom));

        return insets;
    }
}
```

### 2. Remove old soft input mode settings

Delete any calls to:
```csharp
// Remove these — they no longer work
App.Current.On<Android>().UseWindowSoftInputModeAdjust(WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize);
Window.SetSoftInputMode(SoftInput.AdjustResize);
```

### 3. (Optional) Animate smoothly

Add to your `.csproj` to get smooth keyboard animations:

```xml
<AndroidUseWindowInsetsAnimationCompat>true</AndroidUseWindowInsetsAnimationCompat>
```

This uses the AndroidX `WindowInsetsCompat` API which is the modern replacement and works on Android 11+ natively (back-ported via AndroidX on older versions). Your bottom input bar will now slide up with the keyboard.
